records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tyler J Wright in court with attorney Jason Daniel Baltz.  Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1-
Court ordered defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction; credit for 3 days time served. Court will allow the defendant to have release for work and school. Court will allow the defendant to receive good time. 

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 12 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Participate in at least one counseling session for a duration of no less than two hours on healthy sexual relationships and provide proof of attendance to agent;
2) Comply with all rules as set forth by agent;
3) Court ordered the defendant be supervised as a routine misdemeanant, not under the sex offender unit; 
4) Be enrolled in school full time. If not in school full time, be employed for at least 30 hours per week;
5) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
6) Pay DNA surcharge during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
7) No contact with the victim or her residence with the exception of incidental contact in school;

Per the Court, defendant to provide a DNA sample. 

Court will defer ruling on restitution until a restitution hearing. Parties to advise the Court if a stipulation is reached. 

Expungment is authorized by the Court upon successful completion of probation. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.  Restitution hearing scheduled for July 29, 2015 at 08:30 am.
